description:
Replace k_panic() in lora_transition() and lora_transition_from() with error returns.

Locations: lines 94, 100, 120, 125

Current:
  if (new_state >= LORA_STATE_COUNT) {
      LOG_ERR("Invalid state: %d", new_state);
      k_panic();
  }

Target:
  if (new_state >= LORA_STATE_COUNT) {
      LOG_ERR("lora_l2: invalid state (%d), forcing ABORTED", new_state);
      atomic_set(&current_state, LORA_ABORTED);
      return -EINVAL;
  }

Update function signatures:
- lora_transition() currently returns 0 always; change to return -EINVAL on error
- Callers must check return value
